Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[,kɔmpi'lei∫n]
*danh từ
 ■sự biên soạn, sự sưu tập tài liệu
 ■tài liệu biên soạn, tài liệu sưu tập
 ■(tin học) sự biên dịch

Anh - Anh
compilation
■ noun
1》 the action or process of compiling.
2》 a thing, especially a book or record, compiled from different sources.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
compilation
▸ noun COLLECTION, selection, anthology, treasury, compendium, album, corpus, collectanea; pot-pourri.

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
compilation
n.
1) to do, make a compilation
2) a compilation from (various sources)

sentences.en: "Compile time" is the amount of time required to perform a compilation of a program.

sentences.en: It is probably a compilation of Roman and Greek recipes, some or all of them drawn from manuscripts that were later loss.

sentences.en: Most of the popular benchmarks tend to gloss over the joint impact of the operating system and compilation tools on execution time.

sentences.en: The General Statistics Office (GSO) is responsible for the management of statistical activities and is the lead agency for the compilation of social statistics.
